Outlook is currently available in various versions, and Microsoft is looking to consolidate them into the aptly named One Outlook. Previously referred to as Project Monarch, the app includes not only an email component, but also a calendar. Originally due for release last year, it is now looking as though One Outlook is going to be available for limited testing some time in the spring. Wider scale beta testing is expected to start in the summer, but the timetable remains flexible. See also: Microsoft is forcibly upgrading some Windows 10 computers Microsoft seems to have changed its mind about killing&#8230; <a href="https://betanews.com/2022/01/25/microsoft-could-launch-its-new-one-outlook-app-as-early-as-spring/" rel="nofollow">[Continue Reading]</a>